Hi @Francks11!

No, the scroll widget is not included in the "jquery.tablesorter.widgets.js" file. You can see what is included in that file, by default, in the main documentation under [Demos](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#demos) and looking for the red dagger &dagger;

To get all the files, you can go to the [Download section](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#Download) in the main documentation, or on the [main repository page](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter), you can download everything by clicking on the "Download ZIP" button. I would recommend updating all the files, meaning the core & other widgets you are using.

If you already have everything updated and only need the scroller widget, go to the file in the repository directly: https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/widgets/widget-scroller.js. Click the "Raw" button and download it from there.

Here is a [fiddle](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/856bzzeL/143/) - while creating it, I have no idea why it works so beautifully on the main demo page, but looks like crud in the fiddle... I'll have to look at the code again later today.

As for the minimum code required, this needs to be in the header:

```html
<script src="js/jquery-latest.min.js"></script>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/theme.blue.css">
<script src="js/jquery.tablesorter.js"></script>
<script src="js/jquery.tablesorter.widgets.js"></script>
<script src="js/widgets/widget-scroller.js"></script>
```

and the initialization code:

```js
$(function(){
	$('table').tablesorter({
		theme: 'blue',
		widgets: [ 'zebra', 'scroller' ],
		widgetOptions : {
			scroller_height : 300,
			scroller_fixedColumns : 2
		}
	});
});
```

What specifically are you asking about?

The default [`inputs` parser](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/parsers/parser-input-select.js#L18-L28) only handles text. I guess I could include an additional parser in the "parser-input-select.js" file for numeric only inputs (maybe of type number?).

```js
$.tablesorter.addParser({
	id: "inputs-numeric",
	is: function(){
		return false;
	},
	format: function(s, table, cell) {
		var v = $(cell).find('input').val() || s,
			n = $.tablesorter.formatFloat((v || '').replace(/[^\w,. \-()]/g, ''), table);
		return n && typeof n === 'number' ? n : n ? $.trim( s && table.config.ignoreCase ? s.toLocaleLowerCase() : s ) : s;
	},
	parsed : true, // filter widget flag
	type: "numeric"
});
```

You can add the above widget, *and* load the "parser-input-select.js" file for the extra code to make this work.

