@JDWarner @stefanv 
1. How is the implementation of this to be done ? As in, should there be a function evaluating the haar feature at a point (x,y) and for a two rectangle feature of (h,w). 

Evaluating a two rectangle horizontal feature: 

    def haar_feature(x,y,h,w):
    bright = (i[x+h-1,y+w-1]+i[x-1,y-1])-(i[x-1,y+w-1]+i[x+h-1,y-1])       
    dark = (i[x+2*h-1,y+w-1]+i[x+h-1,y-1])-(i[x+h-1,y+w-1]+i[x+2*h-1,y-1])
    haar_feature = bright-dark    
