@jordonwii Underscores are not valid in hostnames. Django's validator doesn't accept underscores either.

If the Django code is validating `"my_subdomain"` for you, you're probably running copypasted code under Python 2 without `unicode_literals` enabled. In that case the regex pattern gets built incorrectly and will match things it shouldn't match.

Try changing `"ul = '\u00a1-\uffff'"` to `ul = u'\u00a1-\uffff'"` (or use Python 3) and notice how the URL doesn't validate anymore.

